# Implementation Plan: Altrosyn Automation (Final)

This document outlines the technical architecture and implementation strategy for the Altrosyn Automation project.

## 1. Objectives
- Automated form filling using Semantic AI.
- Centralized queue management.
- Real-time UI visibility.
- Robust handling of dynamic and custom web elements.

## 2. Technical Stack
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express, Socket.io, Puppeteer.
- **Frontend**: React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Lucide icons.
- **AI**: Google Generative AI (Gemini Flash).

## 3. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Orchestration Layer
- [x] Create [server.js](file:///e:/final%20kabilan%20altrosyn/server/server.js) to handle API requests and websocket connections.
- [x] Implement [queueManager.js](file:///e:/final%20kabilan%20altrosyn/server/queueManager.js) for thread-safe task processing.
- [x] Set up logging system for audit trails and debugging.

### Phase 2: AI Automation Engine
- [x] **LLM Layer 1 (Parsing)**: Implement DOM extraction prompt in [llmService.js](file:///e:/final%20kabilan%20altrosyn/server/llmService.js).
- [x] **LLM Layer 2 (Mapping)**: Implement data-to-field mapping logic.
- [x] **Execution Helper**: Build Puppeteer interaction logic in [automationService.js](file:///e:/final%20kabilan%20altrosyn/server/automationService.js) with specific focus on:
    - Custom ARIA-based radio selection.
    - Listbox dropdown handling.
    - Automated form submission detection.

### Phase 3: Dashboard & Monitoring
- [x] Develop React dashboard with real-time queue updates.
- [x] Implement log downloading for post-task analysis.
- [x] Add status-based UI indicators (Pending, Processing, Waiting Input, Completed, Failed).

## 4. Verification Strategy
- **Unit Testing**: Isolated Gemini connectivity check via [test-gemini.js](file:///e:/final%20kabilan%20altrosyn/server/test-gemini.js).
- **Integration Testing**: End-to-end flow verification via [verify_submission.js](file:///e:/final%20kabilan%20altrosyn/server/verify_submission.js).
- **UI Testing**: Manual submission and real-time update validation in the browser.

## 5. Deployment Notes
- Ensure `CHROME_PATH` is correctly set for the target environment.
- Gemini API key must have sufficient quota for heavy DOM extraction tasks.
